About Us
Glass Lewis is a trusted ally to more than 1,300 investors globally who use our corporate governance research, custom policy recommendations, engagement services and tools, and industry-leading proxy vote management solution to help drive value across their governance activities. We also work with over 3,000 corporate issuer clients, providing research reports, thought leadership, customized voting policies, equity plan models, and opportunities for direct engagement on material governance and disclosure practices.
Glass Lewis’ industry-leading research and analysis covers more than 30,000 meetings each year across approximately 100 global markets. Our clients include many of the world’s leading pension funds, mutual funds, and asset managers, collectively managing over $40 trillion in assets. We have teams located across the United States, Europe, and Asia-Pacific regions, giving us global reach with a local perspective on the most important governance issues. Founded in 2003, Glass Lewis is headquartered in San Francisco, California with additional offices in Kansas City, Missouri; London, U.K.; Paris, France; Limerick, Ireland; Karlsruhe, Germany; Stockholm, Sweden; Manila, Philippines; Toronto, Canada; Sydney, Australia; Timișoara, Romania; and Tokyo, Japan. Our team includes more than 400 full-time employees globally, over half of which are dedicated to research. For more information, please visit www.glasslewis.com.

POSITION OVERVIEW
The EMEA Director of Research is responsible for the oversight of the Manila based branch of the EMEA Research Team. Senior Manila based EMEA Research Team members, including senior research analysts and analyst (supervisors), may report directly to the EMEA Director of Research.
The EMEA Director of Research will provide oversight for the production of reports from the Manila based branch of the EMEA Research Team (involves collaboration with EMEA Based Research Leaders). The role may include delegation and collaboration on a range of subjects. The role will also require collaboration with and the regular provision of feedback to EMEA Research Senior Leadership.

RESPONSIBILITIES 
·         Oversight of the Manila based branch of the EMEA Research Team;
·         Act as escalation point for internal queries on research in the region;
·         Review, edit and publish certain levels of Proxy Papers produced by the Manila based branch of the EMEA Research Team;
·         The role may involve the management of certain projects assigned to Manila based team members including the collection of data pertaining to production of research related products;   
·         Collaboration with different offices and departments in several areas including process and team contribution to large scale projects;
·         Collaborating with other regional directors on resource sharing at different stages of the year dependant on seasonal peaks for certain markets;
·         Work closely with EMEA Research Senior leadership and Global Research Leadership providing insight on several key areas including team development, team processes and team culture, among others;
·         Continuous interaction with, and providing feedback to, senior management in order to identify department-level priorities; and
·         Ensuring company policies and guidelines are clearly communicated to the research team.

QUALIFICATIONS 
·         BA/BS degree and 10+ years of experience in an active corporate governance research role, including at least 3 years in a senior position;
·         Fluency in English; High Proficiency in other European languages (including German, French, Italian, Portuguese and Spanish) are desired but not essential;
·         Demonstrated success in mentoring and coaching;
·         Broad knowledge of corporate governance principles, legal and regulatory frameworks and emerging industry trends
·         Strong time-management, problem solving and people skills;
·         Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, including senior-level business writing and presentation skills (oral and written);
·         High level of proficiency with online applications and business software (MS Office).

This role is a full-time, hybrid position that requires regular office attendance (3x per week). This position is based in our Makati City office.
Join our team and contribute to the accuracy and integrity of our research data. Apply now to become a part of our growing organization!

EEO Statement:
Glass Lewis is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all qualified individuals, regardless ofage, gender identity, religion, disability, or background.

What you'll be doing
Providing comprehensive calendar management for our principal;
Organizing and coordinating schedules, appointments, events, and travel arrangements;
Handling sensitive and confidential information with the utmost discretion;
Serving as a point of contact for internal concerns with the principal and ensure efficient and constant coordination with the main office and other satellite offices as needed;
Assisting with general administrative tasks, including data entry, filing, and implementation of public service projects;
Supporting the leadership team with special projects and other tasks assigned by the principal as needed.
What we're looking for
Candidates must possess a Bachelor’s degree in any field. Candidates with backgrounds on tourism, hotel management or foreign service fields are welcome to apply;
• Excellent organizational, communication, and interpersonal skills
• Proficiency in Microsoft Office suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook);
• Ability to work independently, prioritize tasks, and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment;
• Strong attention to detail and a commitment to accuracy;
• Proven experience in handling confidential and sensitive information;
• Knowledge of office management best practices and procedures is an advantage.

Game Operations Specialist
Responsible for the daily execution of game operations, ensuring a smooth player experience and achieving platform performance goals.
Key Responsibilities:
Monitor platform game data and player behavior; analyze key metrics such as Net NPL and betting participation, and adjust game order based on performance and operational rules;
Launch new games that meet platform requirements, and promptly remove games or providers under maintenance or non-compliance;
Possesses sharp market insight, proactively identifies high-potential games, and formulates effective game ranking and recommendation strategies to enhance player engagement and retention.
Coordinate and support promotional campaigns in collaboration with game providers;
Work closely with cross-functional teams (Tech, Customer Service, Design, etc.) to ensure smooth activity launches and timely issue resolution;
Generate daily, weekly, and monthly game operation reports with actionable insights and optimization recommendations;
Ensure all platform content and activities comply with regulatory standards (e.g., PAGCOR requirements), and provide corrective reports when necessary.
Qualifications:
Prior experience in game platform or game operations preferred;
Strong data analysis skills and proficiency in Excel and backend configuration processes;
Excellent communication, coordination, and accountability;
Fluent in English is an advantage.

Key Responsibilities:
Plan and execute comprehensive test cases including functionality, compatibility, regression, and end-to-end (E2E) testing;
Identify, reproduce, and track bugs; provide detailed testing reports and verification of fixes;
Collaborate closely with development, product, and design teams to ensure timely issue resolution and smooth version releases;
Support product launch processes, including requirement validation, event configuration, and quality monitoring;
Analyze testing and operational data to propose process and performance optimization strategies.
Qualifications:
Minimum 2 years of experience in game or internet product testing / operations;
Familiar with testing tools and defect management systems (e.g., JIRA, TestRail, Postman, etc.);
Understanding of frontend/backend logic and data workflows is a plus;
Strong analytical thinking, attention to detail, and accountability;
Excellent communication and cross-functional collaboration skills;
Fluent English communication preferred.

